1. Running tests

First of all compile "hist_sfp_test" by:
$ make
Compile "wrs_dump_shmem" in userspace/host_tools/tools by:
$ make -C ../../host_tools/tools
Run tests itself:
$ make test
../bats/bin/bats bats_sfp_test_*.bats
 ✓ Check the presence of wrs_dump_shmem
 ✓ Check the presence of hist_sfp_test
 [...]
 15 tests, 0 failures

2. Updating tests

Update the file "bats_sfp_test_2tests.def" with the new test definitions in the
format:
<test name in the free text>; <first_file_with_the_SFP_database_to_use>; <second_file_with_the_SFP_database_to_use>
for example:
my test; file_a.bin; file_b.bin

Put files file_a.bin and file_b.bin under the directory test_data.
Re-generate file "bats_sfp_test_2tests.bats" by:
$ ./generate_tests.sh bats_sfp_test_2tests.def > bats_sfp_test_2tests.bats
Generate dumps of shmem memory filled by the hist_sfp_test:
$ CREATE_RESULTS=yes ../bats/bin/bats bats_sfp_test_2tests.bats
Last command will create txt files in directory result_data, which will be used
in the future to verify tests' results.
Two last command can be triggered by a command:
$ make create_results

After *.txt files are (re-)generated commit them together with *.bin, *.bats
and *.def files to the repo.
